-- Altri, Bayer, Societe Generale: European Equity Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-03-08T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-07/altri-bayer-societe-generale-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  (SXXP) trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index (SXXP)  rose 0.6 percent to 260.11. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  (SX5P) gained 0.3 percent to 2,446.01. The  Euro Stoxx 50
Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, climbed
0.7 percent to 2,460.77.  3Legs Resources Plc (3LEG)  (3LEG LN): The Isle of Man-based shale-
gas explorer may begin natural-gas production from  Poland ’s
shale formations in two years, according to Chief Executive
Officer Peter Clutterbuck. The company has a partnership with
ConocoPhillips (COP US) in Poland. The shares were unchanged at
70 pence.  Altri SGPS SA (ALTR)  :  Portugal ’s second-biggest pulp-
and-paper producer said profit in 2011 dropped 64 percent to
22.6 million euros ($29.7 million). The shares fell 1.4 percent
to 1.12 euros.  Bayer AG (BAYN)  (BAYN GY): The largest German drugmaker is
weighing a bid for Pfizer Inc.’s (PFE US) animal-health unit and
discussing how to raise funding with banks, said people with
knowledge of the plans. Christian Hartel, a Bayer spokesman,
declined to comment. A Pfizer spokeswoman said the company
hadn’t yet decided on a spinoff or sale. Bayer shares rose 0.6
percent to 53.33 euros.  Societe Generale SA (GLE)  :  France ’s second-biggest bank
named Jean-Francois Mazaud head of its private banking and asset
management unit, replacing Daniel Truchi. The shares increased
3.4 percent to 23.78 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Joseph Ciolli in New York at 
